cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of ADMM for solving large-scale machine learning problems efficiently. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it proposes an asynchronous distributed version of ADMM. Additionally, it may fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it analyzes the convergence conditions and rates of the proposed algorithm. It could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the performance of a distributed algorithm on a network of computing nodes. Finally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for solving optimization problems.
